		"name": "EventEase",
		"description": "**EventEase API**  \n  \nEventEase simplifies event management by providing a robust API to handle users, events, RSVPs, and admin tasks.\n\n### Features:\n\n- **User Management**: Register, login, and manage user details.\n    \n- **Event Management**: Create, update, and view events with support for filtering, sorting, and category management.\n    \n- **RSVP System**: RSVP for events with real-time attendee tracking and capacity management.\n    \n- **Admin Operations**: Full control over user, event, and RSVP data for administrators.\n    \n\n### Usage:\n\n- Each endpoint is equipped with role-based access control and input validation.\n    \n- Follow the authentication requirements and pass the necessary tokens in headers.\n    \n- Refer to example requests and responses in the collection for easy integration.\n    \n\n### Notes:\n\n- Ensure required fields and data formats align with the documented schemas (e.g., ISO date format).\n    \n- Handle error responses gracefully; see response codes and error messages for details.\n    \n\nHappy developing! ðŸ˜Š",
